This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of kidneys in ultrasound images using deep neural networks. The use of pre-trained networks for feature extraction and end-to-end learning also suggests a focus on computer vision techniques. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves the use of deep neural networks for classification and regression tasks. 

The Medical Imaging (cs.MED) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with the segmentation of kidneys in ultrasound images, which is a common task in medical imaging. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is a possibility as the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques for image analysis, which is a common application of AI. 

The Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not explicitly deal with information retrieval, but the use of deep neural networks for feature extraction and classification could be relevant to some information retrieval tasks.
